reviewText: I saw this movie when it first came out in 1959, and I remember it very well to this day. There are some very excellent scenes in the flick and I want to watch it again on DVD. Georgina Cookson is a blonde bombshell and I really enjoyed her scenes involving nude photography. Hazel Court also does a good job. Movies like this are not available on Netflix, and that's too bad. I really enjoy vintage and classic films more than current movies.
a light weight grade b movie filmed on set with little plot or character developement. wouldn't recomend. there are many good crime movies out there from britain to choose from in that time period.
